deck_excerpt: Fun HERO deck focusing on its fusions and Masked HERO monsters rather than just Dark Law and Toadally Awesome!
deck_description: This is a HERO deck build around its fusions, not just around Dark Law & Toadally Awesome! My usual opening is with Elemental HERO Nova Master & Elemental HERO Absolute Zero on the field and an Elemental HERO Honesty Neos in the hand (with something else as well) and possibly a face down, depending on starting first or second. After that, if Absolute Zero is killed it blows up your opponents monsters and if Nova Master is attacked, send Honesty Neos to the GY to boost him to 5100 ATK (beating Utopia the Lightning if you activate it before the battle phase) and then you can draw a card. If the facedown is a Change spell, you can also change Absolute Zero into Acid and wipe out your opponents board (It feels good) Thats just one of many strategies. For draw power you've got Nova Master, Divine Wind, Legacy of a Hero & Supply Squad. Its a fun deck, feel free to make any changes and have fun with it.

deck_excerpt: Spam rank 10s & run over your opponent with these trains.
deck_description: The deck has been slowed down significantly since links, but here it is. Monsters: Express Knight & Derricrane are your main combo pieces with Ruffian Railcar helping to support that combo. (also the field spell helps you get to one or the other) We also run a Kaiju engine with Jizukiru being a level 10 Machine that synergizes with the deck nicely. Exodius is cool for recycling & Cyber End Dragon for another level 10(can't forget Maxx C). Spells: Switchyard is the field spell we need, you can special summon Ruffian off its 1st effect & it changes to a level 10, but you can't deal battle damage to your opponent when you do so. The 2nd effect is what we want, you can pitch a card to the grave & add one of your level 10 trains to your hand. Running 3 Terraforming is essential & scapegoats for links. Now for the on-of list, most are self-explanatory. Raigeki, Kaiju Slumber, Upstart, soul charge, Limiter Removal for otk & Foolish Burial for pitching Ruffian. Also running Skill Drain. For the extra deck, you mostly go into Super Dora & sometimes Gustav Max for burn. Skypalace is pretty situational. Galaxy Destroyer is hilarious if you get his effect off & for wiping the back row & popping pendulum scales. Number 35 & 84 work great together& we finish off with our Link monsters.

deck_excerpt: Fill the field with strong Dark-Attribute Fusion monsters
deck_description:
Use the several Fusion spells and Predaplant Chlamydosundew to Fusion Summon strong Dark Attribute Fusion Monsters.

Frightfur Patchwork is there to search Polymerization and Edge Imp Sabres.

Dragostapelia can negate your oponent's monsters effects by putting a Predator counter on them. You can use your opponent's monsters as Dark type materials with Chlamydosundew to make further Fusions.

Tragoedia makes the perfect Level 8 material to summon Starve Venom Greedy Dragon without using your stronger Fusion monsters as materials or to banishing them to use the revival effect

Scapeghost summons multiple tokens that you can use to Fusion Summon Predaplant Triphyovertum or Dragonecro Nethersoul Dragon

Fusion Recycling Plant  is a strong Field spell card to use on this deck. You will use it most of the times to add  a Chlamydosundew that was used as a Fusion material via its effect to make further Fusion Summons.

  Updated as 8/5/2020

deck_excerpt: Shaddoll + Lightsworn + Sephylon = Yummy
deck_description:
This deck has multiple win conditions.

Obviously, this deck has a huge set of Shaddoll's, so that's the main premise. Sadly, El Shaddoll Construct is banned, so this is the best build in order to go around it, in my opinion. With this deck, there are multiple extra tech's that can help you out when things aren't going your way and your monsters are being destroyed quickly.
The purpose of this deck is primarily to beat down your opponent so you can win with the powerful Shaddoll's and the multitude of Synchro/XYZ Monsters in the extra deck. All these can give you an out to many decks you may face. The Lightsworn Monsters exist from the old deck in which I ran El Shaddoll Construct, but since its ban, I decided to add in Sephylon, The Ultimate Timelord to the mix. I know, replacing an Extra Deck Monster with a Main Deck Monster seems dumb, but listen on. Sephylon needs to be special summoned from your hand by having 10 or more monsters in the Graveyard. Now luckily, Shaddoll's have a useful effect when sent to the Graveyard by card effects, so that helps us with him. In addition to that, the Lightsworn's Raiden & Lyla & the Spell Card Charge of the Light Brigade add some more spiciness to this deck because Raiden can help to get monsters in the Graveyard AND activate effects of the Shaddoll's if they get discarded this way, and Lyla can destroy Spells/Traps that the opponent has either face-down or activated (such as continuous spells/traps or field spells), then she sends more Monsters from the deck to the grave once the turn has ended, hopefully spitting out more Shaddoll's. When the Lightsworn's send Monsters to the Graveyard, a mix of Light & Dark Monsters may lay there, so, the BLS - EotB and the Chaos Sorcerer are there in order to benefit from these. They both have effects to just straight up destroy other Monsters, and they're tough to get by. I've added Rainbow Kuriboh to stop your Opponent's Monsters from attacking, along with Vanity's Fiend, since Vanity's Emptiness is banned. These aren't only extra Monsters for Sephylon, but also extra Light & Dark's for BLS & Chaos Sorcerer.

deck_excerpt: A powerful WATER-based deck that focuses on using cards such as Legendary Fisherman III, White Aura Biphamet and Stronghold Whale.
deck_description:
The focus of the deck is to summon out your boss monsters as soon as possible. The deck considers the following monsters to be "boss mosnters" => Legendary Fisherman III, White Aura Biphamet, White Aura Whale, Stronghold Whale and Poseidra the Atlantean Dragon. These monsters are then protected mainly by Sea Stealth Attack. Some general combos for the deck:
  1. The Legendary Fisherman II + A Legendary Ocean = The Legendary Fisherman III.
  2. Instant Fusion Sea Monster of Theseus + Level 4 (with A Legendary Ocean on the field) = White Aura Dolphin.
  3. Deep Sea Diva => SS Fishborg Launcher or Legendary Atlantean Tridon (with a Legendary Ocean) = Tatsunoko. If you then have a Level 7 in your hand = White Aura Biphamet.
  4. Sea Stealth Attack can Banish an Instant Fusion target and keep it alive after the end phase.
  5. Instant Fusion into Rare Fish can lead to some Rank 4 XYZ plays.
  6. Foolish Burial can be used on Stronghold Whale to SS it from the Graveyard if you have two WATER monsters on the field. This can be particularly useful if you are in urgent need of a Sea Stealth Attack.
  7. Remember! Sea Stealth Attack can be used to effectively protect your monsters from removal, use it! And do not forget about its secondary effect to instantly destroy an opponents monster in battle if you are battling with a Level 5 or higher (and thankfully it's original level of 5 or higher so A Legendary Ocean doesn't impact on this secondary effect).

deck_excerpt: Unleash the power of Obelisk and Slifer by summoning Super Quantum and Quickdraw support, and make them invincible through Mound of the Bound Creator
deck_description:
This Deck's concept is very simple: Summoning an Egyptian God should be a problem for your opponent, in particular if this God cannot be taken down by effects. The most annoying problem of Egyptian Gods is that their Summon is quite slow, as you need 3 monsters to Tribute: this can be resolved with some not so new cards and combos. Main combo families:
  • Super Quantum is the newest tactic I added into this Deck for its easy-to-use and Cyber Dragon-alike style: since Red Layer and Blue Layer can recall each other from Deck or GY, they make really very easy for us to gain the 3 monsters we need to Summon an Egyptian God; in addition, there are many XYZs to Summon if you - for example - don't have any Egyptian God in your hand or that Summon wouldn't be so useful for the play.
  • Quickdraw Synchron, Level Eater & Inferno Reckless Summon are an old-school set that fulls your board with monsters you can use to Synchro Summon some of the classic Yusei Fudo's heroes or to Summon an Egyptian God.
  • Nimble Momonga & Giant Rat are a good defensive strategy if you stuck in a bad situation and you run out of Traps or powerful monsters.
  • Hardened Armed Dragon & Mound of the Bound Creator are to support cards that power up your Egyptian Gods so that they become unaffected by card effects.
The Extra Deck is often used as a plan B, so it contains very strong and bossy XYZs and, on the other hand, some good Synchros; to be honest, I've never actually tested the Link monsters in the Side, but I'm confident those are quite good.

deck_excerpt: True Draco and  Metalfoes combine to make a competitive deck that will stand against the ever-changing meta.
deck_description: This deck is pretty simple to use and get the hang of. It uses the Draco engine and metalfoes for support to pendulum summon the draco's or fuse them to provide support or small draw power. Metalfoes Mythriel is your ace fusion as it helps you recycle your metalfoes in the deck and uses you the opportunity to return a troublesome monster card back to the hand or extra deck. Other fusions are there for support and different options. A variety of different Xyz to help balance the extra deck and to use in sticky situations.  Ash Blossom can be used to stop the drawing of cards which could bring a problem going into other meta decks that use a lot of draw power. Metalfoes fusion stays at 2 just in case it gets banished and it can recycle itself for a draw so its never a bad choice. This deck has been used against all aspects of non-link meta and has done very well against them all. (Link will be added later on to update deck use)

deck_excerpt: Always try to go first turn with this deck, because synchro summons can be easily stopped by set cards. When you have a good hand, this deck is capabl
deck_description: Always try to go first turn with this deck, because synchro summons can be easily stopped by set cards. When you have a good hand, this deck is capable of bringing out cosmic blazar dragon, in the only condition that you know synchro monsters very well and do know how to use a synchro deck. If cosmic blazar is not possible, always try to bring out crystal wing, clear wing, or shooting star. A few tips: 1. cosmic blazar is impossible to summon if there are no level eaters in the graveyard. 2: Stardust dragon is very weak by itself, so always use it to bring out shooting star. 3: Synchro is history. So don't be surprised if a meta deck beat you easily.
